      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KAY JAY MIKI (3) started favourite at his latest appearance at Bathurst but had to work to find the front and couldn't see it out. Had come from the back row for second in his previous two outings, one of them at this circuit and distance. Has the benefit of a good draw so can make amends. SATELLITE SIMBA (7) looks close to a win after back-to-back placings, coming from the back row for a 2.2m second at his latest appearance at Bathurst. Two-time winner at this venue and should enjoy a nice smother from this draw. If he gets the gaps he could break through. THEYCALLMEBRUCE (10) may need some luck from the back row but gave a good sight when he led and stuck on for third at Bathurst last time out. DESIDERIO (5) didn't do a bad job when he led from a similar draw and stuck on okay for fourth at Bathurst last time out. First four player.",
